ldives%2C%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20said%20he%20will%20ensure%20that%20the%20small%20Island%20nation%20%26quot%3Bhas%20no%20foreign%20military%20presence%20on%20its%20soil%26quot%3B.%20Soon%20after%2C%20during%20a%20meeting%20with%20Union%20Minister%20Kiren%20Rijiju%2C%20the%20President%20formally%20requested%20New%20Delhi%20to%20withdraw%20its%20military%20personnel.%20Indian%20government%20souces%20have%20said%20the%20two%20sides%20have%20agreed%20to%20discuss%20%26quot%3Bworkable%20solutions%26quot%3B%20to%20continue%20the%20use%20of%20Indian%20military%20platforms%20by%20the%20island%20nation%20as%20they%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20its%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndian%20Troops%20In%20the%20Maldives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20just%20about%2070%20soldiers%20in%20the%20island%20nations.%20These%20personnel%20operate%20India-sponsored%20radars%20and%20surveillance%20aircraft.%20Indian%20warships%20in%20the%20region%20help%20patrol%20the%20country's%20exclusive%20economic%20zone.%20According%20to%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20his%20office%2C%20President%20Dr%20Muizzu%20acknowledged%20the%20significant%20role%20of%20two%20Indian%20helicopters%20in%20numerous%20emergency%20medical%20evacuations.%20This%20small%20group%20of%20Indian%20soldiers%20have%20been%20stationed%20in%20the%20Maldives%20for%20several%20years%20now.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20had%20said%20India's%20cooperation%20with%20Maldives%20is%20based%C2%A0on%20jointly%20addressing%20shared%20challenges%20and%20priorities.%20India's%20assistance%20and%20platforms%20that%20have%20contributed%20significantly%20in%20public%20welfare%2C%20humanitarian%20assistance%2C%20disaster%20relief%2C%20and%20in%20combating%20illegal%20maritime%20activities%20in%20the%20island%20nation%2C%20the%20ministry%20had%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Geopolitical%20Hotspot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20island%20nation%20about%20one-fifth%20the%20size%20of%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Maldives%20is%20home%20to%20about%205%20lakh%20people%20and%20is%20a%20popular%20tourist%20destination.%20But%20amid%20the%20growing%20strategic%20signficance%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20region%20and%20border%20tensions%20between%20key%20Asian%20players%20India%20and%20China%2C%20the%20island%20has%20become%20a%20geopolitical%20hotspot.%20Both%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Beijing%20have%20invested%20generously%20in%20development%20in%20the%20island%20as%20part%20of%20a%20long-term%20geopolitical%20outlook.%20While%20the%20Maldives%20President%20has%20stressed%20that%20it%20wants%20to%20work%20together%20with%20both%20India%20and%20China%2C%20he%20has%20underlined%20that%20the%20island%20nation%20is%20%26quot%3Btoo%20small%20to%20be%20entangled%20in%20geopolitical%20rivalry%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20China%20Angle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Muizzu%20succeeds%20Ibrahim%20Mohamed%20Solih%2C%20whose%20tenure%20saw%20a%20boost%20in%20ties%20between%20the%20island%20nation%20and%20New%20Delhi.%20A%20former%20minister%20and%20Mayor%20of%20Male%2C%20President%20Muizzu%20is%20close%20to%20former%20President%20Abdulla%20Yameen%2C%20who%20borrowed%20heavily%20from%20Beijing%20during%20his%20tenure%20from%202013%20to%202018.%20A%20year%20back%2C%20Muizzu%20had%20told%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20that%20he%20wanted%20stronger%20ties%20with%20Beijing%20should%20his%20party%20win%20the%20elections.%20%26quot%3BWe%20look%20forward%20to%20returning%20to%20government%20in%202023%2C%20with%20President%20Yameen%20at%20the%20helm%2C%20to%20script%20a%20further%20chapter%20of%20strong%20ties%20between%20our%20two%20countries%2C%20both%20domestically%20and%20internationally%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%20When%20Yameen%20was%20barred%20from%20contesting%20the%20election%20because%20of%20a%20criminal%20conviction%20and%20an%2011-year%20jail%20term%20for%20corruption%2C%20he%20nominated%20Muizzu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Balancing%20Game%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20election%20to%20the%20top%20post%2C%20Muizzu%20has%20pushed%20for%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20Indian%20troops%20from%20the%20Maldives%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20security.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20our%20security%2C%20I%20will%20draw%20a%20red%20line.%20The%20Maldives%20will%20respect%20the%20red%20lines%20of%20other%20countries%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20after%20being%20sworn%20in.%20He%20has%20clarified%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20AFP%20that%20he%20does%20not%20intend%20to%20upend%20the%20regional%20balance%20by%20replacing%20Indian%20military%20with%20Chinese%20troops.%20The%20Maldives%20President%20is%20clearly%20trying%20to%20strike%20a%20fine%20balance%20in%20its%20ties%20with%20India%20and%20China.%20In%20his%20meeting%20with%20Union%20Minister%20Rijiju%2C%20he%20discussed%20the%20progress%20in%20projects%20India%20is%20backing%20in%20the%20Maldives.%20%26quot%3BPresident%20Dr%20Muizzu%20and%20Minister%20Kiren%20Rijiju%20concluded%20the%20meeting%20with%20a%20renewed%20commitment%20to%20fortify%20the%20bilateral%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700373360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Flnc9ralg_maldives-prez-meeting_625x300_19_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-maldives-ties-kiren-rijiju-mohamed-muizzu-why-new-maldives-president-wants-indian-troops-out-of-the-island-nation-4586485%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Addressing%20the%20inauguration%20event%20on%20his%20elevation%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Maldives%2C%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20said%20he%20will%20ensure%20that%20the%20small%20Island%20nation%20%26quot%3Bhas%20no%20foreign%20military%20presence%20on%20its%20soil%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.n