%20undergrowth%20and%20shrubbery%2C%20and%20in%20the%20best%20tradition%20of%20jugaad%20that%20defines%20a%20wide%20spectrum%20of%20its%20operational%20activity%2C%20as%20well%20as%20that%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%2C%20it%20also%20constructed%20a%20makeshift%20mud%20ramp%20to%20substitute%20for%20specialised%20off-loading%20equipment%2C%20simply%20unavailable%20at%20the%20remote%20ALG.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20inputs%20from%20the%20helicopter%20reconnaissance%20mission%20over%20Dharasu%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98non-routine%20critical%20delivery%E2%80%99%20mission%20featured%20two%20C-130J-30%E2%80%99s%20from%20the%20IAFs%2077%20%E2%80%98Veiled%20Vipers%E2%80%99%20Squadron%20at%20Hindan%2C%20on%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20outskirts%2C%20and%20was%20ably%20completed%20in%20under%20five%20hours.%20The%20IAF%20declared%20that%20the%20entire%20operation%20was%20underscored%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98calculated%20approach%20and%20adequate%20risk%20mitigation%E2%80%99.%20Its%20success%2C%20it%20added%2C%20stemmed%20from%20%E2%80%98pinpoint%20execution%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20other%2C%20larger%2C%20Boeing%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III%20air%20lifters%2C%20too%2C%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20tunnel%20rescue%20operations.%20One%20of%20them%20shipped%2022%20tons%20of%20heavy%20equipment%20from%20Indore%20to%20Uttarakhand%E2%80%99s%20capital%20Dehradun%2C%20from%20where%20it%20was%20shipped%20to%20Dharasu%20by%20road%2C%20for%20onward%20transshipment%20to%20the%20accident%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IAFs%20daredevil%20Dharasu%20delivery%20operation%20was%20reminiscent%20of%20its%2017%20daring%20flights%2C%20featuring%20C-130J-30%E2%80%99s%20and%20C-17s%2C%20which%20were%20undertaken%20earlier%20this%20year%20as%20part%20of%20Operation%20Kaveri%20to%20repatriate%20thousands%20of%20Indians%20from%20war-torn%20Sudan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fiaf-c17-aircraft-rescue-mission-sudan%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20some%20of%20these%20C-130J-30%20flights%2C%20which%20were%20executed%20in%20pitch%20darkness%2C%20with%20calmness%20and%20dexterity%20on%20the%20unfamiliar%20Wadi%20Sayyidna%20airstrip%20that%20had%20neither%20any%20navigational%20approach%20aids%20nor%20critical%20landings%20lights%2C%20some%2040%20km%20north%20of%20the%20Sudanese%20capital%20Khartoum%2C%20wracked%20by%20civil%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20fleet%20of%2012%20C-130J-30s%2C%20inducted%20into%20service%202011%20onwards%2C%20are%20split%20between%20the%2077%20Squadron%20at%20Hindan%20and%20the%2087%20%E2%80%98Wings%20of%20Valour%E2%80%99%20Squadron%20at%20Panagarh%20in%20the%20east%2C%20from%20where%20they%20support%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20deployment%20along%20the%20disputed%20line%20of%20actual%20control%20(LAC)%20with%20China.%20The%20IAFs%2011%20C-17s%20operated%20as%20part%20of%20No%2081%20%E2%80%9CSkylords%E2%80%99%20squadron%2C%20also%20from%20Hindan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20aircraft%20types%20were%20acquired%20via%20the%20Foreign%20Military%20Sales%20(FMS)%20route%2C%20with%20the%20C-130J-30%E2%80%99s%20costing%20around%20%242-2.5%20billion%20and%20the%20C-17s%20priced%20at%20around%20%244.1%20billion.%20In%20recent%20times%2C%20both%20platforms%20had%20been%20instrumental%20in%20transporting%20army%20personnel%20%E2%80%93%20and%20their%20assorted%20assets-like%20tanks%20and%20infantry%20combat%20vehicles%20%E2%80%93%20to%20the%20LAC%20to%20counter%20the%20ongoing%20three-year-long%20face%20off%20with%20China%E2%80%99s%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%20had%20last%20acquired%20some%2070-odd%20second-hand%20twin-piston%20engine%20Fairchild%20C-119%20%E2%80%98Flying%20Boxcars%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20US%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20after%20which%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20Washington%20deteriorated%20and%20those%20with%20Moscow%20proliferated%2C%20lasting%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20era%2C%20which%20ended%20only%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%20The%20C-119s%2C%20however%2C%20were%20retired%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20following%20their%20extensive%20employment%20in%20two%20wars%20with%20Pakistan%20in%201965%20and%201971.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20for%20over%20five%20decades%20thereafter%2C%20the%20IAF%20remained%20dependent%20almost%20entirely%20on%20legacy%20Soviet-origin%20transport%20platforms.%20This%20was%20in%20addition%20to%20combat%20aircraft-like%20the%20Ilyushin%20Il-76s%20and%20Antonov%20An-32s%2C%20which%20a%20cross-section%20of%20IAF%20pilots%20maintained%20had%20recently%20been%20%E2%80%98technologically%20outmanoeuvred%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20newly%20inducted%20US%20transports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fully%20automated%2C%20state-of-the-art%20flight%20decks%20of%20both%20the%20US%20models%20fitted%20with%20%2B4%20generation%20avionics%20were%20far%20superior%20to%20those%20of%20the%20two%20Soviet%20transports%2C%20making%20them%20relatively%20effortless%20to%20operate%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20former%20IAF%20transport%20pilot%20said%2C%20declining%20to%20be%20identified.%20Besides%2C%20the%20US%20platforms%20were%20%E2%80%98significantly%E2%80%99%20more%20fuel%20efficient%2C%20requiring%20a%20smaller%2C%20three-person%20crew%20%E2%80%93%20two%20pilots%20and%20a%20loadmaster%20%E2%80%93%20to%20operate%2C%20compared%20to%20five%20personnel%20needed%20for%20an%20Il-76%20and%20four%20for%20an%20An-32%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20ease%20of%20operation%20both%20in%20the%20air%20and%20on%20ground%2C%20the%20US%20transports%20had%20a%2012-week%20maintenance%20cycle%2C%20which%20was%20almost%20three%20times%20higher%20than%20that%20of%20the%20Il-76s%20and%20even%20the%2060-70%20retrofitted%20and%20upgraded%20twin-turboprop%20An-32s%2C%20both%20of%20which%20required%20regular%20servicing%20every%20three%20to%20four%20weeks%2C%20said%20the%20C-17%20pilot%20quoted%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20total%20technical%20life%20cycle%20of%20C-130J-30%20and%20C-17%20engines%2C%20too%2C%20is%20notably%20higher%20%E2%80%93%20almost%2010%20times%20more%20than%20that%20of%20the%20fuel-intensive%20Soviet%20aircraft%20power%20packs%2C%E2%80%9D%20retired%20Air%20Marshal%20V.K.%20Bhatia%20said.%20This%20operational%20aspect%20increased%20platform%20efficiency%20and%20considerably%20reduced%20maintenance%20and%20operating%20costs%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20by%20undertaking%20the%20Dharasu%20delivery%20mission%2C%20the%20IAF%20had%20%E2%80%98stretched%E2%80%99%20the%20C-130J-30%E2%80%99s%20operational%20envelope%2C%20possibly%20even%20a%20little%20beyond%20what%20its%20manufacturers%20Lockheed%20had%20anticipated%20and%20could%2C%20in%20time%2C%20further%20boost%20the%20transport%20platform%E2%80%99s%20commercial%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOr%20as%20the%20adage%20goes%2C%20the%20only%20way%20to%20discover%20the%20limits%20of%20the%20possible%2C%20is%20to%20go%20beyond%20them%20into%20the%20impossible%3B%20or%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20near-impossible%2C%20an%20endeavour%20in%20which%20the%20Indian%20military%20excels%20on%20multiple%20fronts%20in%20exploiting%20its%20assorted%20platforms%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700312417000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18180433%2Fimage-1522.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fiaf-lands-super-hercules-military-transport-aircraft-on-unfeasible-strip-for-tunnel-rescue-mission%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20narrow%20and%20undeveloped%203%2C600%20feet%20advanced%20landing%20ground%20had%20earlier%20been%20declared%20%E2%80%98unsuitable%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20IAF%20for%20C-130J-30%20operations.%20But%20despite%20that%2C%20the%20IAF%20executed%20a%20perilous%20mission%20to%20deliver%20crucial%20equipment%20for%20rescuing%20trapped%20workers%20in%20Uttarakhand'