20his%20bid%20to%20discredit%20the%20Delhi%20state%20government%20and%20force%20it%20out%20of%20power%20in%20the%20national%20capital.%20When%20the%20Kejriwal%20government%20changed%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20liquor%20licensing%20policy%20in%202021%2C%20he%20and%20his%20advisers%20thought%20they%20had%20found%20the%20Achilles%E2%80%99%20heel%20that%20they%20had%20been%20looking%20for.%20Liquor%20is%20not%20only%20the%20cash%20cow%20of%20all%20state%20governments%20in%20the%20country%2C%20contributing%20up%20to%2020%25%20of%20their%20annual%20revenues%2C%20but%20also%20one%20of%20the%20principal%20sources%20of%20kickbacks%20to%20state%20government%20lawmakers%20and%20administrators%20for%20favours%20granted%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Liquor%20Mafia%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Manish%20Sisodia%20replaced%20the%20outmoded%20government%E2%80%99s%20monopoly%20of%20liquor%20sales%20in%20Delhi%2C%20first%20re-imposed%20by%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20Prime%20Minister%20Morarji%20Desai%20after%20a%20brief%20period%20of%20privatisation%20in%20the%20mid-70s%2C%20with%20an%20auction-based%20private%20sales%20system%20for%20liquor%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20advisers%20lost%20no%20time%20in%20unleashing%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20upon%20Kejriwal%E2%80%99s%20government%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20find%20the%20Achilles%E2%80%99%20heel%20that%20it%20was%20sure%20existed%20somewhere%20within%20the%20AAP%20cabinet%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opportunity%20to%20use%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20new%20liquor%20policy%20to%20malign%20and%20discredit%20the%20AAP%20government%20arose%20out%20of%20a%20report%20by%20Naresh%20Kumar%2C%20the%20chief%20Secretary%20of%20Delhi%20to%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%2C%20V.K%20Saxena%2C%20that%20alleged%20a%20variety%20of%20procedural%20lapses%20in%20the%20formulation%20of%20the%20new%20liquor%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fwhat-is-the-delhi-liquor-case-what-are-eds-allegations-against-aap-leaders-8970389%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9Carbitrary%20and%20unilateral%20decisions%E2%80%9D%20taken%20by%20Sisodia%20in%20his%20capacity%20as%20excise%20minister%20had%20resulted%20in%20%E2%80%9Cfinancial%20losses%20to%20the%20exchequer%E2%80%9D%20estimated%20at%20more%20than%20Rs%20580%20crore.%20It%20alleged%20that%20%E2%80%9Ckickbacks%E2%80%A6received%20by%20the%20AAP%20Delhi%20government%20and%20AAP%20leaders%E2%80%9D%20from%20owners%20and%20operators%20of%20alcohol%20businesses%20for%20preferential%20treatment%20such%20as%20discounts%20and%20extensions%20in%20licence%20fee%2C%20waiver%20on%20penalties%20and%20relief%20due%20to%20disruptions%20caused%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Fabout%2Fcoronavirus%2F%5C%22%3ECOVID-19%3C%2Fa%3E%20pandemic%2C%20etc.%20were%20used%20to%20%E2%80%9Cinfluence%E2%80%9D%20the%20assembly%20elections%20held%20in%20Punjab%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Fsection%2Fcities%2Fgoa%2F%5C%22%3EGoa%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fwhat-is-the-delhi-liquor-case-what-are-eds-allegations-against-aap-leaders-8970389%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20early%202022.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20chief%20secretary%20of%20Delhi%2C%20Sharma%20could%20have%20had%20the%20information%20needed%20to%20report%20what%20he%20considered%20%E2%80%9Cirregularities%20in%20procedure%E2%80%9D.%20He%20may%20even%20have%20been%20misled%20by%20his%20officers%20into%20believing%20that%20there%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cheavy%20financial%20losses%20to%20the%20exchequer%E2%80%9D.%20But%20there%20was%20no%20conceivable%20way%20in%20which%20he%20could%20have%20found%20out%20how%20much%20the%20party%2C%20or%20select%20members%20within%20it%2C%20received%20as%20kickbacks%2C%20or%20how%20these%20were%20being%20diverted%20into%20funding%20elections%20in%20other%20states.%20This%20could%20at%20most%20have%20been%20conjecture%2C%20but%20it%20gave%20the%20Modi%20government%20the%20pretext%20it%20wanted%20to%20begin%20its%20onslaught%20on%20the%20AAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fnews%2Fsc-upholds-amendments-to-pmla-giving-ed-unbridled-powers-of-summons-arrests-raids%2Farticle65689464.ece%5C%22%3Ehad%20passed%3C%2Fa%3E%20eight%20amendments%20to%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20in%202019%20that%20gave%20the%20ED%20virtually%20unlimited%20powers%20of%20arrest%20and%20incarceration.%20The%20amendments%20also%20made%20it%20virtually%20impossible%20for%20indicted%20persons%20to%20obtain%20bail%20%3Cem%3Ewithout%20first%20all-but-proving%20their%20innocence.%3C%2Fem%3E%20So%2C%20all%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20needed%20to%20do%20to%20destroy%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20for%20total%20accountability%20to%20the%20electorate%20was%20to%20accuse%20it%20of%20an%20offence%20under%20the%20PMLA%2C%20send%20the%20members%20of%20its%20government%20directly%20responsible%20for%20the%20policy%20to%20judicial%20custody%2C%20and%20keep%20them%20there%20till%20the%20ordinary%20voter%20was%20convinced%20that%20%3Cem%3Ethey%20had%20to%20have%20committed%20some%20irregularity%20that%20justified%20keeping%20them%20in%20jail%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20tactic%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20been%20using%20against%20his%20opponents%20ever%20since%20he%20has%20begun%20to%20feel%20the%20throne%20on%20which%20he%20sits%20starting%20to%20shake.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20his%20first%20target%20was%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20industry%20minister%20and%20a%20key%20figure%20for%20the%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20assembly%20elections%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fed-arrests-delhi-health-minister-satyendar-jain-in-money-laundering-case%5C%22%3ESatyendar%20Jain.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJain%20was%20considered%20a%20%E2%80%98soft%E2%80%99%20target%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20since%202017%2C%20because%20in%20that%20year%2C%20and%20again%20in%202018%2C%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20had%20investigated%20him%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20finding%20something%20indictable%2C%20but%20had%20failed.%20In%202022%2C%20however%2C%20now%20armed%20with%20the%202019%20amendments%20to%20the%20PMLA%2C%20the%20ED%20was%20able%20to%20not%20only%20arrest%20him%2C%20but%20keep%20him%20in%20jail%20for%2017%20months%20without%20trial%2C%20conviction%20or%20even%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%202024%20elections%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20Modi%20has%20started%20to%20feel%20insecure.%20His%20government%20is%20capitalising%20on%20the%20doubt%20that%20Jain%E2%80%99s%20long%C2%A0%20incarceration%20has%20sown%20in%20ordinary%20peoples%E2%80%99%20minds%20to%20redouble%20its%20attacks%20on%20AAP.%20On%20February%2026%2C%20it%20arrested%20Sisodia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESisodia%2C%20too%2C%20has%20now%20been%20in%20jail%20without%20trial%2C%20constantly%20being%20denied%20bail%2C%20since%20February%2026%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchronology-samajhiye-5-days-4-agencies-under-modi-govt-control-target-opposition-journalists-activists%5C%22%3EChronology%20Samajhiye%3A%205%20Days%2C%204%20Agencies%20Under%20Modi%20Govt%20Control%20Target%20Opposition%2C%20Journalists%2C%20Activists%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20eight%20months%20that%20have%20followed%2C%20despite%20scores%20of%20searches%2C%20the%20ED%20had%20not%20been%20able%20to%20find%20a%20shred%20of%20evidence%20that%20would%20justify%20keeping%20Sisodia%20in%20jail%20until%20only%20six%20weeks%20ago%2C%20on%20October%205%2C%20when%20it%20arrested%20an%20AAP%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fenforcement-directorate-conducts-searches-at-aap-mp-sanjay-singhs-house%5C%22%3ESanjay%20Singh.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20grounds%20the%20ED%20gave%20for%20his%20arrest%20were%20beyond%20flimsy%2C%20for%20his%20only%20stated%20crime%20was%20that%20he%20introduced%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Delhi%20%E2%80%9CLiquor%20Mafia%E2%80%9D%20to%20Manish%20Sisodia.%20Considering%20how%20many%20people%20a%20politician%20meets%20every%20day%2C%20one%20doubts%20whether%20Sisodia%20even%20remembered%20his%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjay%20Singh%20had%2C%20however%2C%20been%20arrested%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20information%20given%20by%20a%20businessman%20%E2%80%93%20one%20Dinesh%20Arora%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20himself%20under%20arrest%20at%20the%20time%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Fexcise-policy-case-delhi-court-allows-two-to-turn-approver%2Farticleshow%2F104143419.cms%5C%22%3Ehad%20turned%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20%E2%80%98approver%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20ED.%20The%20ED%20did%20not%20publicise%20the%20reason%20for%20his%20arrest%2C%20but%20admitted%20that%20he%20had%20been%20granted%20freedom%20in%20exchange%20for%20giving%20information%20that%20would%20allow%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20keep%20Sisodia%20in%20jail%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%20of%20time.%20This%20was%20necessary%20because%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20bail%20plea%20was%20coming%20up%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20Sisodia%20in%20jail%20was%20essential%20because%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20ultimate%20target%20was%20Arvind%20Kejriwal.%20Having%20sufficiently%20reinforced%20suspicions%20in%20the%20lay%20public%E2%80%99s%20mind%20by%20first%20arresting%20a%20minister%20and%20then%20the%20iconic%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20AAP%20government%2C%20Modi%20was%20about%20to%20unleash%20the%20ED%20on%20Chief%20Minister%20Kejriwal%20himself.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20businessman-turned-informer%20Dinesh%20Arora%E2%80%99s%20willingness%20to%20turn%20approver%20proved%20invaluable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20Arora%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cinformation%E2%80%9D%2C%20Singh%20was%20arrested%20on%20October%205.%20So%20great%20was%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20hurry%20to%20discredit%20Kejriwal%2C%20that%20the%20ED%20issued%20its%20summons%20to%20him%20barely%20three%20weeks%20later.%20To%20say%2C%20therefore%2C%20that%20these%20arrests%20and%20so-called%20%E2%80%98disclosures%E2%80%99%20were%20designed%20to%20destroy%20the%20credibility%20of%20a%20key%20rival%20political%20party%20only%20months%20before%20the%20next%20general%20elections%2C%20would%20therefore%20be%20an%20understatement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcbi-nia-enforcement-directorate-use-abuse%5C%22%3EThe%20Uses%20(And%20Abuses)%20of%20Investigative%20Agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20truth%20about%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20liquor%20policy%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20far%20Prime%20minister%20Modi%20and%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20will%20pursue%20the%20attack%20on%20Kejriwal%20and%20AAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20about%20the%20new%20liquor%20policy%20that%20the%20Delhi%20government%20introduced%20in%20August%202021%20is%20the%20exact%20opposite%20of%20what%20the%20Modi%20government%20and%20its%20utterly%20tamed%20print%20and%20audio-visual%20media%20outlets%20have%20portrayed%20it%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20%E2%80%98old%E2%80%99%20liquor%20policy%2C%20the%20Delhi%20government%20was%20both%20the%20wholesaler%20and%20the%20retailer%20of%20alcohol%20in%20the%20city.%20The%20government%20paid%20the%20manufacturer%20his%20ex-factory%20price%20plus%205%25%2C%20took%20control%20of%20the%20liquor%20and%20bore%20the%20cost%20of%20transportation%20and%20storage%20till%20the%20retail%20outlets.%20The%20retail%20outlets%20were%20all%20controlled%20by%20the%20government%20but%20licensed%20to%20the%20premise%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20bureaucratic%20wholesale-plus-monopolistic%20retail%20system%20had%20led%20to%20a%20number%20of%20shortcomings%3A%20the%20number%20of%20brands%20of%20any%20particular%20spirit%20stocked%20by%20the%20government%20liquor%20shops%20was%20limited%20and%20not%20responsive%20to%20changes%20in%20public%20tastes%20and%20incomes.%20The%20retail%20liquor%20shops%20were%20unevenly%20distributed%20with%20far%20fewer%20shops%20in%20poorer%20parts%20of%20the%20city.%20Consequently%2C%20a%20greater%20amount%20of%20country%20liquor%20was%20being%20sold%20in%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAAP%E2%80%99s%20new%20policy%20made%20the%20government%20%3Cem%3Eget%20out%20of%20the%20liquor%20trade%20altogether%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20wholesalers%20paid%20a%20tax%20of%2014%25%20on%20their%20sales%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20retail%20trade%20was%20wholly%20privatised%3A%20The%20government%20had%20divided%20the%20city%20into%2032%20zones%2C%20of%20which%2020%20were%20classified%20as%20affluent%2C%20and%20the%20remaining%2012%20as%20relatively%20poor.%20Each%20zone%20was%20divided%20into%20a%20number%20of%20principalities%2C%20each%20to%20be%20served%20by%20up%20to%20three%20retail%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20decided%20the%20number%20of%20retail%20locations%20and%20principalities%20in%20each%20zone%20and%20put%20these%20up%20for%20auction.%20The%20retail%20locations%20were%20evenly%20spaced%20to%20ensure%20that%20every%20%3Cem%3Emohalla%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20every%20section%20of%20the%20population%2C%20had%20equal%20access%20to%20a%20liquor%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20then%20auctioned%20the%20liquor%20shop%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20auction%2C%20the%20government%20garnered%20Rs%205%2C300%20crore%20from%20the%20auction%20of%20locations%20in%20the%20more%20affluent%2020%20zones%2C%20and%20Rs%203%2C180%20crore%20from%20the%20auctions%20in%20the%20remaining%2012%20zones.%20The%20lower%20paying%20capacity%20of%20the%20poorer%20areas%20was%20automatically%20reflected%20in%20the%20lower%20bids%20for%20these%20locations.%20An%20important%20side%20benefit%20of%20the%20new%20policy%20was%20that%20by%20giving%20easier%20access%20to%20licensed%20liquor%20in%20poor%20areas%2C%20it%20reduced%20the%20sale%20of%20illicit%20liquor%20within%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20after%20the%20new%C2%A0%20policy%20came%20into%20operation%2C%20a%20civil%20servant%2C%20who%20withheld%20his%20name%20while%20sharing%20the%20above%20figures%20to%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-excise-revenue-set-to-double-after-licence-auctions-under-new-liquor-policy-101628274483032.html%5C%22%3Etold%20its%20correspondent%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20along%20with%20new%20brand%20licensing%20and%20some%20other%20minor%20taxes%2C%20the%20government%20expected%20to%20garner%20over%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%20a%20year%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20liquor%20in%20the%20capital.%20This%20was%20almost%20double%20the%20average%20of%20Rs%205%2C500-crore%20recorded%20in%20the%20previous%20three%20years%2C%20and%20the%20excise%20revenue%20of%20Rs%205%2C272%20crore%20(excluding%20VAT)%20that%20was%20garnered%20between%20September%201%2C%202022%20and%20August%2031%2C%202023%20after%20the%20return%20to%20the%20old%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20entire%20liquor%20trade%20was%20privatised%2C%20and%20all%20allotments%20were%20made%20through%20public%20auction%2C%20where%20did%20the%20space%20remain%20for%20graft%20and%20favouritism%3F%20In%20the%2018%20months%20since%20Jain%20was%20imprisoned%2C%20no%20newspaper%20has%20asked%20this%20question.%20The%20omission%20speaks%20volumes%20for%20the%20moral%20decay%20that%20has%20settled%20into%20journalism%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn2%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-hounding-of-the-aam-aadmi-party%23_ftnref2%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700308805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F18161034%2FScreen-Shot-2020-02-18-at-4.08.52-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-hounding-of-the-aam-aadmi-party%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20his%20first%20year%20in%20office%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20targeted%20every%20political%20leader%2C%20every%20political%20party%2C%20and%20every%20institution%20that%20could%20become%20a%20threat%20to%20his%20ambition.%20Paradoxically%2C%20the%20party%20he%20seems%20to%20fear%20the%20most%20is%20the%20smallest%20among%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20major%20constituents%20%E2%80%93%20%C2%A0the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-hounding-of-the-aam-aadmi-party%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shakira%20handed%20Latin%20Grammy%20award%20by%20rival%20of%20footballer%20ex-partner%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700307480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-sergio-ramos-shakira_6364594.jpg%3F20231118121044%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fshakira-handed-latin-grammy-award-by-rival-of-footballer-ex-partner-13010866%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Singer%20Shakira%20won%20big%20at%20this%20year's%20Latin%20Grammys%20-%20including%20for%20a%20track%20which%20took%20a%20swipe%20about%20former%20partner%20and%20footballer%20Gerard%20Pique.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A287%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fshakira-handed-latin-grammy-award-by-rival-of-footballer-ex-partner-13010866%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fshakira-handed-latin-grammy-award-by-rival-of-footballer-ex-partner-13010866%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fshakira-handed-latin-grammy-award-by-rival-of-footballer-ex-partner-13010866%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Economy%3A%20Is%20It%20Really%20That%20Bad%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18150619%2FDown-graph-p.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%2044%20years%20after%20independence%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20development%20and%20prospects%20aroused%20little%20enthusiasm%2C%20whether%20among%20Indians%20or%20western%20commentators.%20Things%20started%20changing%20after%20the%20reforms%20of%20the%20Narasimha%20Rao%20led%20government%20in%201991.%20That%20much-celebrated%20economic%20liberalisation%20aligned%20well%20with%20the%20zeitgeist%20in%20the%20Western%20world%3A%20a%20shrinking%20role%20for%20government%20and%20a%20celebration%20of%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20accompanied%20by%20relentless%20homilies%20about%20globalisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarratives%20of%20profound%20economic%20change%20erupted%2C%20and%20haven%E2%80%99t%20stopped%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20now%2C%20we%20have%20heard%20and%20read%20about%20the%20emerging%20phenomenon%20that%20is%20India.%20It%20has%20been%20hailed%20as%20a%20potential%20superpower%2C%20a%20sleeping%20giant%2C%20a%20great%20untapped%20market%20and%20a%20country%20finally%20reclaiming%20its%20supposedly%20deserved%20spot%20on%20the%20global%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20image%20clashes%20with%20reports%20of%20continuing%20poverty%20and%20deprivation%2C%20dangerously%20high%20pollution%2C%20urban%20decay%2C%20crumbling%20infrastructure%2C%20an%20overwhelmed%20judicial%20system%20and%20horrific%20atrocities%20in%20the%20name%20of%20religion%20and%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20presents%20a%20case%20of%20cognitive%20dissonance%20that%20is%20difficult%20to%20reconcile%2C%20not%20just%20for%20outsiders%2C%20but%20for%20Indians%20as%20well.%20Is%20India%20doing%20well%2C%20or%20poorly%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20ways%20to%20examine%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20performance%20since%20independence.%20One%20is%20to%20compare%20it%20with%20its%20own%20past%2C%20under%20British%20misrule.%20The%20other%20is%20to%20compare%20it%20to%20what%20other%20countries%20managed%20to%20achieve%20within%20the%20same%20or%20similar%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20national%20income%20statistics%20for%20India%20began%20to%20be%20compiled%20only%20after%20independence%2C%20estimates%20of%20growth%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rug.nl%2Fggdc%2Fhistoricaldevelopment%2Fmaddison%2Freleases%2Fmaddison-project-database-2020%5C%22%3EMaddison%20Project%20Database%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20show%20that%20GDP%20grew%20only%20by%200.9%25%20per%20year.%20Population%20growth%20of%200.8%25%20per%20year%20meant%20that%20per%20capita%20GDP%20grew%20at%20the%20anaemic%20rate%20of%200.1%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowth%20rates%20picked%20up%20right%20after%20independence%2C%20and%20notwithstanding%20all%20the%20flaws%20of%20successive%20governments%2C%20the%20stark%20contrasts%20provide%20a%20clear%20indictment%20of%20British%20imperialism%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ftrillion-dollar-economy-india%5C%22%3EAverting%20a%20%2410-Trillion%20Dystopia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20there%20has%20been%20significant%20economic%20growth%20after%20independence%20is%20not%20in%20doubt.%20First%2C%20during%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%20grew%20at%20over%203%25%20annually.%20There%20was%20a%20clear%20deceleration%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20which%20was%20reversed%20by%20much%20higher%20growth%20rates%20over%20the%20next%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20commonly%20held%2C%20but%20demonstrably%20false%20view%20is%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20high%20growth%20phase%20began%20only%20after%20the%20reforms%20of%20the%20early%201990s.%20The%20data%20show%20that%20the%20phase%20actually%20began%20a%20decade%20earlier%2C%20with%20the%20growth%20rate%20over%20the%201980s%20being%20almost%20identical%20to%20that%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20much-improved%20economic%20growth%20relative%20to%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20twentieth%20century%2C%20the%20growth%20rates%20in%20the%20first%20three%20decades%20after%20independence%20led%20to%20much%20disappointment%2C%20dashed%20expectations%2C%20and%20the%20coinage%20of%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20rate%20of%20growth%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disappointment%20arose%20from%20an%20obvious%20comparison%20with%20the%20contemporary%20economic%20performance%20of%20other%20countries%3A%20India%E2%80%99s%20rate%20of%20growth%20from%201950%20to%201980%20was%20slower%20than%20the%20world%20average%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20average%20for%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20line%20of%20reasoning%20is%20to%20claim%20that%20India%20is%20%3Cem%3Esui%20generis%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20there%20is%20no%20other%20country%20quite%20like%20ours%2C%20so%20comparisons%20are%20not%20meaningful.%20This%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20an%20evasive%20manoeuvre.%20There%20is%20much%20that%20India%20can%20learn%20from%20the%20experience%20of%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20comparisons%20with%20Western%20nations%20are%20a%20stretch%2C%20due%20to%20their%20history%20of%20imperialism%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20industrial%20revolutions%20of%20the%20eighteenth%20and%20nineteenth%20centuries%20had%20their%20provenance%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20much%20better%20peer%20group%20consists%20of%20Asian%20countries%2C%20several%20of%20which%20were%20victims%20of%20imperialism%2C%20and%20were%20starting%20with%20very%20similar%20initial%20conditions%20circa%201950.%20The%20numbers%20below%20show%20that%20several%20of%20these%20countries%20did%20better%20than%20India%20in%20terms%20of%20growth.%20Vietnam%20was%20the%20exception%2C%20but%20it%20was%20plagued%20by%20the%20French%20and%20American%20wars%20until%201975.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18145644%2Fsnapshot-1700299535548.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18145644%2Fsnapshot-1700299535548.png%20840w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18145644%2Fsnapshot-1700299535548-300x48.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685309%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22134%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECalculations%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rug.nl%2Fggdc%2Fhistoricaldevelopment%2Fmaddison%2Freleases%2Fmaddison-project-database-2020%5C%22%3EMaddison%20Project%20Database%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20important%20questions%20that%20arise%20from%20comparing%20GDP%20growth%20across%20countries%2C%20the%20GDP%20level%20and%20its%20growth%20rate%20have%20turned%20into%20an%20unhealthy%20obsession%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEveryone%20knows%20that%20India%20has%20the%20fastest%20GDP%20growth%2C%20is%20the%20third%20or%20the%20fifth%20largest%20economy%2C%20and%20that%20the%20level%20will%20reach%20X%20trillion%20some%20years%20from%20now%2C%20where%20X%20is%20five%2C%20or%20twenty%2C%20or%20thirty%2C%20or%20whatever%20number%20the%20speaker%20feels%20like%20throwing%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20popular%20level%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20five%20trillion%2C%20though%20some%20ruling%20party%20members%20have%20had%20trouble%20specifying%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2F_7awsBrQRpM%3Fsi%3DLGApeUmDR8QwzSgI%5C%22%3Enumber%20of%20zeros%20in%20a%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20have%20confused%20a%20five%20trillion%20dollar%20economy%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Ft_d_h_nair%2Fstatus%2F1228274062834618368%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Efive%20million%20ton%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20have%20counselled%20us%20to%20not%20to%20get%20into%20the%20maths%20since%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Fvideo%2F937105%2Fa-5-trillion-economy-dont-get-into-those-growth-rate-maths-piyush-goyal-advises-business%5C%22%3Eallegedly%20never%20helped%20Einstein%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20laughable%20innumeracy%20lies%20a%20blinkered%20collective%20view%20of%20development%20which%20derives%20a%20bizarre%20kind%20of%20pride%20from%20the%20size%20of%20the%20economy.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20pointing%20out%20that%20elementary%20algebra%20tells%20you%20that%20there%20is%20nothing%20remarkable%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20level%20reaching%20five%20trillion%20dollars%20in%20a%20few%20years%20from%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%202023%20budget%20documents%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20was%20estimated%20to%20be%20Rs%20273.1%20trillion%2C%20or%20%243.3%20trillion%20at%20the%20current%20exchange%20rate%20of%20Rs%2083%20per%20dollar.%20To%20get%20to%20%245%20trillion%2C%20the%20dollar%20value%20of%20the%20GDP%20needs%20to%20grow%20by%2052%25%2C%20or%20by%208.7%25%20per%20year%20in%20nominal%20terms%20if%20we%20choose%20a%20horizon%20of%205%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssuming%20a%20rupee%20depreciation%20of%20about%204%25%20per%20year%20means%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20nominal%20GDP%20in%20rupees%20has%20to%20grow%20by%20about%2012.7%25%20per%20year.%20For%20expected%20real%20GDP%20growth%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20we%20can%20use%20the%20average%20since%201980%2C%20which%20is%20about%205.6%25%20per%20year.%20A%20reasonable%20value%20for%20expected%20inflation%20is%205%25%20per%20year%2C%20which%20gets%20us%20to%20about%2010.6%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20short%20of%20the%2012.7%25%20required%2C%20but%20a%20slight%20tweaking%20of%20expected%20real%20growth%20rates%2C%20or%20inflation%2C%20or%20rupee%20depreciation%2C%20will%20make%20the%20calculation%20work.%20If%20the%20tweaks%20seem%20unrealistic%2C%20we%20can%20always%20move%20the%20goalposts%20and%20say%20we%20will%20get%20there%20in%20six%20or%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthe-many-economic-guarantees-and-promises-of-the-modi-government%5C%22%3EThe%20Many%20Economic%20Guarantees%20and%20Promises%20of%20the%20Modi%20Government%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20point%20is%20that%20getting%20to%20a%20five-trillion-dollar%20economy%20in%20five%20to%20seven%20years%20requires%20no%20major%20policy%20innovations%2C%20grand%20vision%20or%20administrative%20brilliance.%20If%20the%20economy%20performs%20as%20it%20has%20for%20the%20last%20few%20decades%20on%20average%2C%20we%20will%20get%20there%20simply%20by%20the%20magic%20of%20compounding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetting%20aside%20the%20calculation%2C%20the%20notion%20of%20a%20high%20GDP%20level%20as%20a%20dominant%20concern%20is%20troubling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Nobel-winning%20economist%20Joseph%20Stiglitz%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fgdp-is-the-wrong-tool-for-measuring-what-matters%2F%5C%22%3Eexplains%20lucidly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20measure%20is%20very%20limited%20in%20its%20scope%20and%20applicability%20to%20understanding%20public%20welfare.%20As%20a%20measure%20of%20development%2C%20its%20drawbacks%20are%20well-known%3A%20it%20says%20nothing%20about%20the%20distribution%20of%20income%2C%20it%20ignores%20non-market%20transactions%20in%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20and%20it%20does%20not%20account%20for%20the%20steep%20cost%20of%20environmental%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20these%20problems%20with%20the%20concept%20itself%2C%20there%20are%20significant%20measurement%20difficulties%20and%20statistical%20issues%20connected%20to%20how%20the%20numbers%20are%20produced.%20No%20wonder%20that%20economists%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20reported%20numbers%20for%20India%20as%20well%20as%20for%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20narrow%20focus%20on%20a%20single%20indicator%20such%20as%20the%20GDP%20was%20a%20late-20th%20century%20phenomenon%2C%20amplified%20by%20multilateral%20institutions%20like%20the%20World%20Bank%20and%20the%20IMF.%20Contrary%20to%20this%2C%20even%20elementary%20economics%20textbooks%20tell%20you%20that%20there%20are%20at%20least%20three%20main%20macroeconomic%20variables%3A%20output%2C%20employment%20and%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDevelopment%20economists%20have%20suggested%20measures%20of%20welfare%20combining%20multiple%20indicators%2C%20while%20also%20advocating%20for%20a%20dashboard%20of%20economic%20measures%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20single%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20we%20think%20that%20the%20metrics%20suggested%20by%20development%20economists%20are%20difficult%20to%20measure%2C%20India%20would%20do%20well%20to%20shift%20its%20focus%20to%20the%20other%20two%20main%20macroeconomic%20variables%20according%20to%20textbooks%3A%20employment%20and%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20clear%20that%20opposition%20parties%20intend%20to%20highlight%20these%20two%20issues%20in%20the%202024%20elections.%20Remarkably%2C%20these%20were%20exactly%20the%20same%20issues%20that%20caused%20much%20political%20turmoil%20fifty%20years%20ago%2C%20in%201974%2C%20in%20the%20eventual%20leadup%20to%20the%20Emergency.%20That%E2%80%99s%20clear%20evidence%20for%20civilisational%20continuity%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FAeRJvIWkfVI%3Fsi%3DelXfpXc3h9AIYJQI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20200px)%2085vw%2C%20200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18142229%2FIndia-is-Broken-200x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18142229%2FIndia-is-Broken-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F18142229%2FIndia-is-Broken.jpg%20400w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685303%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAshoka%20Mody%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%20is%20Broken%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EStanford%20University%20Press%20(February%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshoka%20Mody%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20is%20Broken%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20a%20great%20antidote%20to%20blinkered%20growth-focused%20thinking.%20The%20superbly%20crafted%20book%20highlights%20that%20any%20fair%20evaluation%20of%20the%20economy%20has%20to%20answer%20the%20question%20of%20how%20growth%20has%20benefitted%20India%E2%80%99s%20people%20at%20large.%20It%20is%20simultaneously%20a%20political%20history%20and%20a%20sustained%20critique%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20scathing%20judgements%20are%20telegraphed%20in%20its%20table%20of%20contents%3A%20we%20have%20%E2%80%9CPart%201%3A%20Fake%20Socialism%2C%201947-1964%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CChapter%2010%2C%20India%20Has%20an%20Empress%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CChapter%2016%2C%20Rajiv%20Unleashes%20the%20Gale%20Force%20of%20Hindu%20Nationalism%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9CChapter%2021%2C%20Modi%20Pushes%20the%20Economy%20off%20the%20Edge%E2%80%9D%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20searing%20indictment%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20economy%20over%20the%20last%2075%20years%20is%20a%20refreshing%20change%20from%20the%20relentless%20boosterism%20of%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20decades%20or%20the%20anodyne%20assessments%20of%20many%20commentators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20popular%20narrative%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20post-independence%20economic%20history%20has%20congealed%20around%20a%20combination%20of%20stylised%20facts%20and%20mindless%20repetition%20of%20uninformed%20myths%3A%20Nehru%20was%20a%20socialist%20and%20was%20responsible%20for%20the%20low%20rates%20of%20growth%3B%20the%20licence-permit%20raj%20under%20Indira%20and%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20strangulated%20the%20economy%20until%20the%20reforms%20of%20Narasimha%20Rao%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%20liberated%20it%3B%20there%20is%20something%20called%20the%20Gujarat%20model%3B%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%20was%20done%E2%80%9D%20in%2070%20years%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMody%20does%20an%20excellent%20job%20of%20demolishing%20these%20nuggets%20of%20received%20wisdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20particularly%20clear-eyed%20about%20Nehru%2C%20offering%20a%20bracing%20contrast%20to%20the%20hagiography%20of%20many%20writers.%20As%20he%20points%20out%2C%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20socialism%20was%20mostly%20rhetorical%2C%20bearing%20little%20resemblance%20either%20to%20Soviet%20socialism%20or%20to%20European%20social%20democratic%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20even%20the%20label%20Fabian%20socialism%20is%20misapplied%20to%20Nehru%2C%20since%20the%20exemplar%20of%20that%20variety%2C%20Clement%20Attlee%2C%20pioneered%20free%20health%20care%2C%20secondary%20education%20and%20social%20insurance%20in%20the%20UK%20%E2%80%93%20all%20conspicuously%20absent%20in%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20economic%20thrust%20of%20the%20Nehru%20years%20was%20heavy%20industry%2C%20aligned%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20big%20push%20industrialisation%2C%20which%20was%20popular%20at%20the%20time.%20Mody%20thinks%20this%20was%20a%20serious%20mistake%20and%20that%20the%20focus%20should%20have%20been%20on%20labour-intensive%20light%20industry%2C%20which%20would%20have%20generated%20far%20more%20employment%20and%20let%20India%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20post-World%20War%20trade%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unifying%20theme%20in%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%20critique%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20policies%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20focus%20on%20job%20creation.%20This%20is%20a%20powerful%20and%20intuitive%20organising%20principle.%20It%20runs%20as%20a%20consistent%20thread%20through%20independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findia-narendra-modi-jobs-unemployment%5C%22%3EThree%20Claims%20of%20Government%20Economists%20About%20Jobs%20Put%20to%20the%20Test%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20output%20growth%20and%20employment%20are%20positively%20correlated%2C%20but%20the%20magnitude%20of%20this%20correlation%20is%20unusually%20low%20for%20India.%20Low%20unemployment%20and%20good%20jobs%20clearly%20benefit%20individuals%2C%20but%20also%20have%20enormous%20social%20impact%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20a%20commonplace%20observation%20in%20many%20societies%20that%20unemployed%20youth%20provide%20fertile%20recruiting%20grounds%20for%20all%20manner%20of%20political%20violence%2C%20and%20India%20is%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaking%20job%20creation%20a%20priority%20%E2%80%93%20through%20budgetary%20allocations%20and%20policies%20favouring%20labour-intensive%20manufacturing%20with%20an%20export%20orientation%20%E2%80%93%20does%20not%20mean%20giving%20up%20on%20GDP%20growth%2C%20as%20shown%20by%20Japan%2C%20Korea%2C%20Taiwan%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMody%20references%20the%20work%20of%20A.K.%20Ghose%20to%20estimate%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20jobs%20shortfall%20was%20already%20at%20a%20staggering%2020-25%20million%20in%201955.%20The%20situation%20only%20worsened%20in%20subsequent%20decades%2C%20with%20the%20backlog%20reaching%2030-35%20million%20in%201965%2C%2040-45%20million%20by%20the%20mid-1980s%2C%2058%20million%20in%202000%20and%20at%20least%2080%20million%20by%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20much-touted%20demographic%20dividend%2C%20to%20be%20realised%20from%20a%20bulging%20youth%20population%2C%20has%20the%20flip%20side%20that%20it%20will%20require%20an%20additional%20seven%20to%20nine%20million%20jobs%20per%20year.%20These%20numbers%20demonstrate%20the%20futility%20of%20focussing%20on%20GDP%20growth%20alone%20%E2%80%93%20India%E2%80%99s%20best%20GDP%20growth%20phase%2C%20from%202003%20to%202011%2C%20did%20little%20to%20make%20a%20dent%20in%20the%20mountain%20of%20the%20jobs%20backlog.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMody%20notes%20that%20the%20high%20growth%20period%20in%20India%20was%20driven%20by%20a%20finance%20and%20construction%20boom%2C%20which%20did%20not%20create%20enough%20new%20jobs.%20More%20generally%2C%20this%20phenomenon%20of%20%E2%80%98jobless%20growth%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20noted%20widely%2C%20and%20is%20a%20result%20of%20much%20of%20the%20growth%20happening%20in%20the%20services%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20missteps%20going%20back%20to%20the%201950s%2C%20India%20seems%20to%20have%20skipped%20the%20intermediate%20stage%20of%20a%20transition%20from%20a%20primarily%20agricultural%20economy%20to%20an%20industrial%20one%2C%20directly%20going%20to%20a%20service%20sector-dominated%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20development%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20jobs%20is%20compounded%20by%20the%20failure%20in%20developing%20human%20capital.%20This%20failure%20began%20in%20the%20Nehru%20era%2C%20and%20has%20continued%20ever%20since%2C%20as%20described%20in%20detail%20by%20Amartya%20Sen%20and%20Jean%20Dreze%20in%20their%202013%20book%20%3Cem%3EIndia%3A%20An%20Uncertain%20Glory%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F6rQAfuvIWv8%3Fsi%3DqeeA-wr1q-tdy1LX%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEducation%20and%20health%20expenditures%20have%20lagged%20behind%20world%20averages%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time.%20It%20is%20not%20as%20if%20this%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20realised%20early%20on.%20Back%20in%201966%2C%20the%20Kothari%20commission%20recommended%20that%206%25%20of%20national%20income%20be%20devoted%20to%20education.%20Sadly%2C%20this%20target%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20achieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMody%20makes%20the%20case%20that%20India%20has%20delayed%20the%20provision%20of%20public%20goods%20such%20as%20education%2C%20health%20care%20and%20infrastructure%20for%20far%20too%20long.%20There%20has%20been%20progress%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%2C%20primary%20school%20enrolment%20is%20now%20near%20universal%20in%20India%2C%20but%20the%20quality%20of%20education%20remains%20very%20poor.%20The%20neglect%20of%20primary%20education%20results%20in%20low%20worker%20productivity%2C%20which%20erodes%20the%20advantage%20of%20low%20labour%20costs%20in%20Indian%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlongside%20the%20many%20economic%20insights%2C%20Mody%20also%20focuses%20on%20what%20he%20calls%20a%20Catch-22%20situation%20%E2%80%93%20the%20erosion%20of%20norms%20and%20accountability%2C%20the%20restoration%20of%20which%20would%20require%20accountability.%20One%20only%20needs%20to%20think%20of%20regular%20reports%20from%20UP%20and%20Bihar%2C%20among%20other%20states%2C%20to%20see%20that%20erosion%20of%20norms%20and%20accountability%20is%20an%20uncharacteristically%20restrained%20phrase%20to%20describe%20the%20high%20corruption%2C%20white-collar%20thievery%20and%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20it%20is%20notable%20that%20the%20rot%20had%20started%20early.%20Mody%20notes%20that%20Nehru%20was%20already%20dismissing%20concerns%20about%20corruption%20in%20the%20late%201950s%20and%20that%20in%20August%201962%2C%20home%20minister%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20said%20in%20parliament%20that%20the%20government%20had%20punished%2020%2C000%20officials%20for%20corruption%20over%20the%20previous%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Santhanam%20committee%20report%20in%201963%20highlighted%20a%20culture%20of%20corruption%20in%20government%20%E2%80%93%20apparently%20the%20going%20commission%20rate%20for%20PWD%20contracts%20was%20between%207%25%20and%2011%25%20at%20the%20time.%20That%20indicative%20metric%20has%20jumped%20four%20to%20sixfold%2C%20if%20the%20%E2%80%9840%25%20%3Cem%3Esarkara%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20allegations%20are%20anything%20to%20go%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Ten%20Factors%20to%20Remember%20Amidst%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Win%20and%20BJP's%20Defeat%20in%20Karnataka%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkarnataka-democracy-modi-shah%5C%22%3ETen%20Factors%20to%20Remember%20Amidst%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Win%20and%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Defeat%20in%20Karnataka%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20years%2C%20political%20corruption%20reached%20the%20very%20top%2C%20with%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%2C%20her%20heir%20apparent%20and%20poster%20boy%20for%20undeserved%20privileges%2C%20becoming%20the%20focal%20point%20for%20Congress%20party%20funds.%20Stories%20of%20briefcases%20of%20cash%20changing%20hands%20in%20exchange%20for%20business%20licenses%20and%20permits%20during%20this%20era%20abound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusting%20yet%20another%20myth%20about%20bureaucratic%20control%20arising%20from%20socialism%20during%20the%20Nehru%20era%2C%20Mody%20traces%20the%20origins%20of%20the%20notorious%20%E2%80%98license-permit%20raj%E2%80%99%2C%20quoting%20from%20I.G.%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20memoirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImport%20licensing%20was%20simply%20an%20%3Cem%3Ead%20hoc%3C%2Fem%3E%20response%20to%20dwindling%20foreign%20exchange%20reserves%20in%20late%201956%20and%20early%201957%20due%20to%20the%20heavy%20import%20demands%20of%20the%20second%20five-year%20plan.%20It%20took%20on%20a%20life%20of%20its%20own%20and%20soon%20led%20to%20industrial%20licensing%2C%20and%20to%20many%20creative%20opportunities%20for%20lobbying%20and%20political%20contributions%20by%20businesses%20in%20pursuit%20of%20their%20interests.%20Today%E2%80%99s%20crony%20capitalism%20is%20just%20a%20newer%20version%20of%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20primary%20attraction%20of%20Mody%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20that%20it%20is%20a%20narrative%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20post-independence%20political%20economy%20and%20not%20simply%20an%20account%20of%20policy%20mis-steps%20and%20economic%20shocks.%20The%20book%20provides%20a%20well-informed%20and%20sceptical%20evaluation%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%2C%20most%20importantly%20of%20the%20disconnect%20between%20decades%20of%20pious%20rhetoric%20and%20underwhelming%20eventual%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%20is%20said%20and%20done%2C%20what%20is%20the%20answer%20to%20the%20simplistic%20question%3A%20is%20India%20doing%20well%20economically%3F%20Mody%E2%80%99s%20book%20says%20it%20is%20not%2C%20with%20its%20title%20reflecting%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20downbeat%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%2C%20how%20does%20one%20square%20this%20with%20the%20lived%20experience%20of%20many%20Indians%3F%20They%20see%20the%20six-lane%20expressways%2C%20Vande%20Bharat%20trains%2C%20malls%2C%20shiny%20airports%2C%20gated%20multi-storied%20apartment%20buildings%20(with%20separate%20lifts%20for%20the%20help)%2C%20UPI%20and%20a%20hundred-plus%20unicorns.%20They%20are%20only%20dimly%20aware%20of%20another%20India%20in%20which%20people%20are%20struggling%20to%20find%20jobs%20while%20battling%20the%20spiralling%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20poverty%2C%20deprivation%20and%20social%20injustice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20difficulty%20is%20that%20these%20two%20portraits%20of%20India%20are%20simultaneously%20true%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20leads%20to%20the%20clashing%20narratives%20and%20cognitive%20dissonance.%20There%20is%20some%20truth%20to%20what%20has%20long%20been%20a%20cliche%3A%20you%20can%20make%20a%20good%20case%20for%20every%20generalisation%20about%20India%20as%20well%20as%20its%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoes%20this%20mean%20that%20the%20two%20views%20are%20only%20different%20in%20their%20perception%20about%20the%20metaphorical%20glass%20being%20half%20full%20or%20half%20empty%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20quite.%20Economic%20growth%20has%20benefited%20middle%20and%20upper-class%20Indians%20the%20most.%20This%20is%20a%20significant%20fraction%2C%20but%20not%20a%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20one-third%20of%20Indian%20households%20earn%20more%20than%20Rs%205%20lakh%20per%20year%2C%20and%20can%20be%20classified%20as%20middle%20or%20upper%20class%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fmiddle-class-nearly-1%2F3rd-of-indias-population-to-be-2%2F3rds-by-2047-report%2Farticleshow%2F95239621.cms%5C%22%3Eone%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20November%202022.%20This%20segment%20dominates%20the%20political%20and%20media%20discourse%2C%20and%20thinks%20that%20the%20country%20is%20doing%20just%20fine.%20The%20remaining%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20population%20is%20struggling%2C%20in%20one%20way%20or%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20fair%20to%20say%20then%2C%20that%20the%20glass%20is%20two-thirds%20empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVijay%20Poduri%20is%20a%20quantitative%20finance%20researcher%20based%20in%20the%20San%20Francisco%20bay%20area.%20He%20has%20a%20Ph.%20D.%20in%20Physics%20and%20is%20a%20CFA%20charterholder.%20He%20has%20a%20deep%20interest%20in%20economic%20history%20and%20development%20and%20is%20working%20on%20a%20book%20on%20the%20prosperity%20of%20nations.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700307015000%2C%22vi